Subject: Re: [T2] oil in air intake

At 12:10 AM 01/02/2000, you wrote:
>  That mayonaise looking stuff that you find
>under the oil cap when a water cooled car is leaking water into the oil. I am
>thinking that this is most likely caused by worn rings creating blow-by. Would
>this be the most common cause?

The most common cause is short run driving. Just clean it all during 
periodic maintenance.

>  I have also noticed that my oil starts to smell
>like gas after awhile. This would also be caused by blow-by correct?

The most common cause is short run driving. Just change the oil more often 
during periodic maintenance. Also, make sure the mixture is adjusted properly.
